						<summary>

						<p>Vijayanagara, Rāmadēva-Mahārāya, Śaka 15[4]2, Raudri, Uttarāyaṇa, Mithuna = A.D. 1630.</p>						

						<p>A woman called Aṅgāḷammaṉ dug a tank, constructed a <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> with the Vināyaka image consecrated in it and also made provision for offerings to the temple of Chokkanāthasvāmi at Namaṉkurichchi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vaḍaveḷi-Ambalavāṇatuṟai, all for the merit of Vīrappa-Pūchchaiya-Nāyakkar.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 760.]</p>						

